4 in target housing or child-occupied facilities, who willfully violates the standards
5 for performing lead-hazard detection or lead-hazard abatement procedures included
6 in the administrative regulations promulgated pursuant to KRS 211.9075 shall be
7 guilty of a Class D felony.
8 (7) The penalties provided in subsections (5) and (6) of this section are cumulative and
9 are in addition to any other penalties, claims, damages, or remedies available at law
10 or in equity.
11 (8) Any person who violates any provisions of KRS 211.760 shall be fined not less
12 than ten dollars ($10) nor more than one hundred dollars ($100). Each day of
13 violation or noncompliance shall constitute a separate offense.
14 (9) Any person who violates any provision of Section 1 of this Act shall be guilty of a
15 Class D felony.
